{"id":8575,"date":"2021-12-09T07:46:00","date_gmt":"2021-12-09T06:46:00","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/saltinourhair.com\/?p=8575"},"modified":"2021-12-22T22:47:28","modified_gmt":"2021-12-22T21:47:28","slug":"places-to-visit-sri-lanka","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.saltinourhair.com\/sri-lanka\/places-to-visit-sri-lanka\/","title":{"rendered":"10 Best Places to Visit in Sri Lanka"},"content":{"rendered":"<div class=\"wp-block-group\"><div class=\"wp-block-group__inner-container\">\n<div class=\"wp-block-group\"><div class=\"wp-block-group__inner-container\">\n<h2 id=\"todo\">1. Visit the Nine Arch Bridge in Ella<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Nine Arch Bridge is one of the most iconic places to visit in the whole of <a href=\"https:\/\/www.saltinourhair.com\/sri-lanka\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Sri Lanka<\/a>. This mammoth bridge is located just outside the pretty town of <a href=\"https:\/\/www.saltinourhair.com\/sri-lanka\/ella-sri-lanka\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Ella<\/a>, deep among luscious jungle, green tea plantations, and bamboo forest. At a massive 25 meters high and 91 meters long, the bridge is an example of incredible architecture and engineering; it has stood without steel support for over 100 years! <\/p>\n<\/div><\/div>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-gallery columns-2 is-cropped\"><ul class=\"blocks-gallery-grid\"><li class=\"blocks-gallery-item\"><figure><div class=\"image-wrapper\"><div class=\"fake-image\"><\/div><noscript><img src=\"https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/11\/21205320\/must-do-sri-lanka-ella-Nine-arch-bridge-train-2-648x810.jpg\" alt=\"best visit sri lanka nine arch bridge\"><\/noscript><img width=\"270\" height=\"338\" alt=\"best visit sri lanka nine arch bridge\" data-id=\"72041\" data-full-url=\"https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/11\/21205320\/must-do-sri-lanka-ella-Nine-arch-bridge-train-2.jpg\" data-link=\"https:\/\/w